title: Eutelsat : share price downturn, a broker's analysis
full_text: Eutelsat is down more than 1% in Paris, as Berenberg announced on Tuesday that it had lowered its target price for Eutelsat Communications from 11.6 to 7.1 euros.The research firm - which is maintaining its 'hold' recommendation on the stock - is not totally convinced by the satellite operator's planned merger."The big debate surrounding Eutelsat remains its planned merger with OneWeb", the analyst points out in a research note.We believe that the magnitude of the short-term dilutive impact on earnings and cash flow, in addition to the increased risk profile of the new entity, are likely to keep investors who have traditionally positioned themselves in the satellite and telecoms sectors on the sidelines, at least for the time being", concludes Berenberg.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: UBS raises target for FMC to 38 euros - 'Neutral
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX) - Swiss major bank UBS raised its price target for FMC from 30 to 38 euros and left its rating at "neutral". His slightly lowered estimate for operating earnings (Ebit) is more than offset by his lowered estimates for capital expenditures and acquisitions, analyst Graham Doyle justified the new price target for the dialysis specialist's stock in a research note published Tuesday. title: Worldline: share price up, broker adjusts his recommendation
full_text: Worldline gained nearly 2.5% in Paris, as Morgan Stanley raised its recommendation on the stock this morning from 'weight in line' to 'overweight', with an unchanged target price of 51 euros.In a research note, the analyst believes that the payment services specialist stock has all the attributes of the 'growth at a reasonable price' (GARP) investment philosophy.Worldline offers both attractive and defensive growth characteristics, underpinned by rising inflation and structural factors (erosion of cash, increasing card use, market share gains at the expense of banks)", he points out in the note."With a PER to 2024 of 13x for organic growth of 8% to 10% and growth in operating margin before depreciation and amortization (OMDA) of around 15%, we see all the qualities inherent in the GARP concept", concludes the intermediary. title: Adidas leave Puma far behind after recommendations
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Two analyst recommendations attracted some investors to Adidas on Tuesday. However, a liberating blow in the chart failed to materialize. The papers of the Herzogenauracher climbed with plus 2.5 percent to 141.84 euros back to its 50-day line. In the weaker market environment, however, it put the brakes on a further rise. Puma, on the other hand, lost up to 3 percent after a downgrade.      Analyst Olivia Townsend of JPMorgan is optimistic, particularly ahead of Adidas' detailed annual results on March 8, and therefore also gave the shares "Positive Catalyst Watch" status. Her price target of 162 euros is just above the year-to-date high. Townsend is betting on surprise potential in 2024 in particular, after market expectations have come back massively following three profit warnings. Alluding to the new Adidas CEO Björn Gulden, she speaks of a "Gulden Opportunity".      Berenberg's Graham Renwick is also betting that Gulden will come clean with the outlook, especially given his reputation for "promising little and then delivering more." This would create a "clean base" for 2024, Renwick said. He even trusts the shares to reach 180 euros, a return to the interim highs from the summer of 2022.      For Puma, on the other hand, Townsend now only rates it "neutral". Puma remains a good long-term growth and margin story, and will also do well in 2023. However, Adidas simply has more potential at the moment.      Adidas is also ahead on an annual basis with a plus of 10 percent compared to Puma with a plus of 6 percent. The previous year did not go well for either, with the share price halving./ag/mis

title: Berenberg upgrades Adidas to 'Buy' - Target raised to 180 euros
full_text: HAMBURG (dpa-AFX Broker) - Private bank Berenberg upgraded Adidas to "buy" from "hold" and raised its price target to 180 euros from 160 euros. The market has become too cautious with regard to the sporting goods maker's profitability, and he himself downgraded the stock in September after three profit warnings, analyst Graham Renwick wrote in a research note presented Tuesday. There should still be headwinds in 2023, but new chief Björn Gulden has cleared the air with the new outlook, he said. He also has a reputation for promising less than he delivers, he added. With the right strategy and its implementation, as well as investments, Adidas is in a good position for the important sports year 2024, he said. Renwick's operating earnings (Ebit) estimate for the coming year is 30 percent above the consensus forecast, according to his own figures. And even on their basis, Adidas is trading at a 20 percent discount to Nike, he pointed out./gl/ck      Publication of the original study: 27.02.2023 / 18:05 / GMT  First disclosure of original study: Date not specified in study / Time not specified in study / Time zone not specified in study----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Michelin: share price rises, one analyst more positive
full_text: Michelin's share price rose on Monday following a recommendation upgrade by Goldman Sachs, which sees the horizon clearing for the French manufacturer after its recent underperformance.At around 2:15 pm, the French tire manufacturer's share price gained 3.1%, making it the second-biggest gainer on the Paris CAC 40 index, which was up 1.6% at the same time.Goldman Sachs, which has upgraded its rating to 'buy' from 'neutral' on the stock, points out that the share has underperformed the sector along with its rivals Continental and Pirelli since the start of the year, a discrepancy the analyst attributes to the cautious outlook communicated by the Clermont-Ferrand-based group.However, after what he expects to be a difficult first quarter, Michelin should benefit from the second quarter onwards from a recovery in volumes, a favorable price effect and a decline in raw material and transportation costs, he stresses.The American bank has therefore raised its price target from €27 to €35, indicating a potential upside of around 20%.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: ALTEN :  Oddo raises its target on the stock
full_text: Oddo maintains its Outperform rating on Alten shares, with a price target raised from €165 to €176. title: ICADE :  Invest Securities lowers its target
full_text: Invest Securities maintains its buy recommendation on Icade shares, with a price target reduced from 60 to 57.2 euros.  No solution in terms of Icade Santé's liquidity has yet been agreed, but it would probably include the sale of all or part of Icade's stake in Icade Santé", says the research firm.Despite the attractiveness of an increased payout and a share buyback limiting dilution in a scenario involving the full disposal of Icade Santé (E2.6 billion), a scenario involving the disposal of 58% of the stake (E1.5 billion) would enable Icade to retain a substantial proportion of healthcare assets (16%) to offset the difficulties of the tertiary asset portfolio and the volatility of the property development business', the broker believes. Invest Securities believes that a partial or full disposal could be positive in the short term, but more questionable in the long term. In any case, "both scenarios point to potential stock market appreciation over the next year", says Invest. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Metzler lowers BASF to aSella - Not much to gain 2023
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Bankhaus Metzler downgraded BASF to "sell" from "buy" and cut its price target to 41 euros from 59 euros. The outlook for the chemical group's cash inflow has deteriorated with a view to the coming years, analyst David Varga wrote in a research note presented on Monday. The increase in planned investment raises concerns that free cash flow from operations will not be sufficient to cover the dividend until the China Verbund fully starts production. In addition, the company's management has been cautious about the recovery in demand, partly because there are no signs of China's hoped-for recovery. He also said the company plans to shut down the TDI plant in Ludwigshafen, which would be an advantage for competitors. "There is not much to gain this year," Varga concluded of the stock./mis/ag  Publication of the original study: 27.02.2023 / 07:56 / CET First disclosure of the original study: 27.02.2023 / 07:56 / CET

title: Sopra Steria: up 4%, analysts buy the stock
full_text: Sopra Steria's share price rose by nearly 4% at the end of the day, benefiting from two positive analyses.Oddo maintains its outperform rating on Sopra Steria shares, with a price target raised from 214 to 236 euros. The analyst is basing his opinion on the company's better-than-expected results for the 2022 financial year, including organic growth of 8% in Q4, compared with the consensus of 6% and Oddo's 6.4%, and ROA of 453 ME, 3% above expectations, reflecting a MOA of 8.9%, up 80 points.Management is positive about demand, which remains strong at the start of 2023, reports Oddo. Sopra Steria is thus targeting organic growth of 3 to 5% in 2023 (Oddo is at 3.1%, consensus at 2.9% pre-publication) as well as MOA slightly above 9%. Believing that this is 'a very good publication from Sopra Steria', the analyst points out that the only bad news comes from the difficulties encountered at SFT. The problem is not so much the short-term financial impact, which is fairly negligible, but rather the impact this will have on the Group's ambitions for SBS in Germany.  Following this publication, we are raising our forecasts for organic growth in 2023 and 2024 to 4.7% and 4.8% respectively (compared with 3.1% and 4.0%)", concludes the broker.Considering the valuation to be "out of line with the fundamentals", Invest Securities also reiterates its "buy" opinion on Sopra Steria, with a price target raised from 198 to 228 euros, "convinced that the rerating that began in early 2023 should be extended, and even amplified".The analyst points out that "2022 achievements are solid and, above all, 2023 guidance is reassuring, with even the possibility of the company doing better due to the very cautious scenario adopted for the second half of the year".  In addition, non-operating factors (IS, provisions, Axway) and the integration of the CS Group and Tobiana acquisitions have had a significant impact, which leads us to raise our expectations quite significantly", he continues.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: Berenberg announced on Friday that it had raised its price target for AXA from 32 to 33 euros, following yesterday's positive surprise on share buybacks announced on the occasion of the company's 2022 annual results.The French insurance giant announced yesterday the immediate launch of a share buyback program of up to 1.1 billion euros, an announcement that surprised the market according to the analyst.According to the intermediary, the surprise came mainly from the management team's stated intention to propose a payout ratio of 70% of operating income, in the form of both share buybacks and dividends.For Berenberg, maintaining this level of shareholder remuneration appears tenable over the long term, as does continuing to buy back shares at a rate of around 1.1 billion euros.The professional therefore maintains his buy recommendation on the stock.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: On Friday, Stifel raised its recommendation on Accor from 'sell' to 'hold', with a price target raised from 20 to 32 euros, welcoming the 'solid' results unveiled yesterday by the hotel group.In a note published in the morning, the analyst considers that the risk/return profile of the stock appears 'more attractive' following the publication and a conference call deemed 'convincing'.'Although operating leverage could have been more convincing last year, it should improve over time', writes the intermediary in its study.Combined with the improved RevPAR momentum, this raises our estimates above consensus", it adds.Stifel indicates that it is considering other potential catalysts, such as shareholder redistributions, but considers that these are currently outweighed by more unfavorable factors, in this case concerns about strategy and a stock market valuation judged to be "stretched".In spite of this, he concludes, his new price target still suggests a 'small' potential for appreciation.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: CARMAT :  Degroof Petercam remains Buy
full_text: Degroof Petercam on Thursday renewed its buy recommendation on Carmat, with a price target of 20.2 euros, following annual results deemed 'unsurprising'.After a fiscal year 2022 marked by the resolution of quality issues on its artificial heart, the year 2023 will be one of business recovery, estimates the Belgian investment house in a research note.According to Degroof, the two main challenges facing the company today are (1) getting production off the ground to meet its annual targets, and (2) extending its financial visibility beyond July 2023.In the short term, however, FDA approval for the resumption of the feasibility study in the USA should be the main catalyst for the stock, continues the Brussels-based firm.Degroof Petercam points out that Carmat plans to keep the market regularly informed of the progress of its Aeson heart, which should give investors a better understanding of the momentum the company will enjoy this year.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: FORVIA  :  Berenberg raises its target price
full_text: Berenberg raised its target price for Forvia from €24 to €25 on Thursday, following the presentation of the group's annual results, which it believes have allayed concerns about its debt situation.The analyst believes that the automotive supplier's strong cash-generating capacity, combined with its €1 billion divestment program, have allayed concerns about what some consider to be "excessive" debt following the acquisition of Hella.For Berenberg, which is maintaining its buy recommendation on the stock, investors will now be able to focus on the Group's solid fundamentals, namely the recovery of its margins and cash flow in a stabilized volume environment.In addition to synergies and cost-cutting measures, adds the intermediary, not to mention the commercial benefits derived from the new joint offering put in place by Faurecia and Hella, he concludes.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: JPMorgan lowers target for Fresenius to 29.60 euros - 'Neutral
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. bank JPMorgan lowered its price target for Fresenius to 29.60 euros from 31.90 euros and left its rating at "Neutral". With the deconsolidation of FMC, the medical group is taking a first step under new management to simplify the group's structure, analyst David Adlington wrote in a research note presented on Thursday. He believes it will ultimately come to selling the remaining shares as well. Leaving these measures aside, 2023 will be a difficult year for subsidiaries FMC, Vamed and Kabi, he said. This led him to significantly lower earnings estimates. For the time being, the stock is "dead money."/tih/gl      Publication of the original study: 23.02.2023 / 06:21 / GMT First circulation of the original study: 23.02.2023 / 06:21 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Credit Suisse raises target for Zalando to 46 euros - 'Outperform
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX Broker) - Swiss bank Credit Suisse raised its price target for Zalando to 46 euros from 33 euros and kept its rating at "outperform." title: KORIAN  :  Oddo reduces its target price
full_text: Oddo maintains its neutral rating on Korian shares, with a price target reduced from €14 to €9. After a year 2022 marked by inflation, Korian has guided for 2023 growth of at least 8% organic, including ~4% price effect, a guidance that comes in below consensus. The market was rather surprised by the scale of the decline", says Oddo.In 2023, capital expenditure will be close to 500 ME, compared with nearly 830 ME in 2022, says the analyst, who indicates that he has adjusted his 2023-2024 projections to take account of the guidance.Oddo also indicates that the Group's refinancing remains a point of uncertainty for the market, with refinancing of around 900 ME planned for 2023. We fear a slight loss of real estate value or a slight increase in the cost of financing, rather than blockages or serious difficulties in refinancing (unlike Orpéa)", says Oddo.According to the analyst, "the configuration at the start of the year still appears to be full of opposing elements. Given the 2023 margin and cash profile, we believe that the timing will not be opportune before the end of 2023'.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: L'Oréal: analyst upgrades to buy, target 450 E
full_text: The stock ended the day in the green, benefiting from a positive analysis by Bank of America. The analyst resumed his coverage of L'Oréal shares on Wednesday, with a Buy recommendation and a target of 450 euros, representing a potential upside of 17%.In a research note, the analyst praises the French cosmetics group's business mix, strong online positioning, marketing know-how and "unparalleled" brand portfolio, which he believes should enable it to accelerate both its market share gains and improve profitability.This performance should, in turn, fuel a solid cash flow that could support more than five billion euros in M&A transactions and the redistribution of 10% of market capitalization in the form of dividends over the next five years, BofA continues.The intermediary adds that the reopening of the Chinese economy and the recovery of tourism in Asia could also generate positive surprises, while deeming that the 20% discount that L'Oréal shares are currently showing in relation to Estée Lauder is not justified in view of the "solid execution" recently demonstrated by the group.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: Worldline: share price down, broker's opinion
full_text: Worldline is down nearly 2% in Paris, while this morning Oddo maintained its outperform rating on Worldline shares, with a price target reduced from €60 to €58.  The stock was down 4% yesterday, mainly due to a disappointing 2023 EBITDA margin guidance (26.4% vs. css at 27.0%), with a weaker-than-expected 2022 pro forma basis (25.4% vs. 26.0% reported)', reports the analyst. Oddo considers this market sanction to be 'a little harsh in view of trends that remain solid in Q4 and a 2023 guidance that is admittedly disappointing in terms of margin, but with an overall unchanged medium-term trajectory'.Nevertheless, the broker believes that the 2023 guidance takes away from the Group's 2024 objective of 'aiming for a margin of 30%'. title: Barclays leaves FMC at 'Equal Weight' - Target 32 euros
full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX Broker) - British investment bank Barclays left its rating on Fresenius Medical Care (FMC) at "Equal Weight" with a price target of 32 euros after figures. The key data for the fourth quarter were not as bad as feared, analyst Hassan Al-Wakeel wrote in a research note presented on Wednesday. Above all, the adjusted earnings per share exceeded expectations, namely by 20 percent. However, he said the focus is likely to be on the outlook, which should be well received by the market. He continues to prefer the shares of the still parent company Fresenius./tih/la  Publication of the original study: 22.02.2023 / 06:51 / GMT First disclosure of the original study: 22.02.2023 / 06:51 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Barclays leaves Fresenius at 'Overweight' - Target 32 euros
full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.K.-based investment bank Barclays left its rating on Fresenius at "overweight" with a price target of 32 euros after key fourth-quarter data. The outlook for 2023 implies some downside to consensus at the midpoint, analyst Hassan Al-Wakeel wrote in a research note issued Wednesday. The focus is probably more on the group structure with a deconsolidation of the dialysis subsidiary Fresenius Medical Care, which is confirmed to be progressing. Such steps would be helpful to remove a discount for the conglomerate structure./tih/la  Publication of the original study: 22.02.2023 / 07:16 / GMT First disclosure of original study: 22.02.2023 / 07:16 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: Morgan Stanley upgrades Wacker Chemie to 'Overweight'.
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. investment bank Morgan Stanley upgraded Wacker Chemie to "overweight" from "equal-weight" and raised its price target to 185 euros from 143 euros. Politically backed plans to boost the solar industry in Western countries offer significant upside potential for the medium-term earnings and market value of Wacker Chemie's polysilicon business, analyst Charles Webb wrote in a research note issued Wednesday. A combination of tax breaks and energy price guarantees would structurally boost the company's profitability and have the potential to make Wacker a cost leader in this industry, rather than a laggard as it has been in the past./edh/la  Publication of the original study: 22.02.2023 / 03:00 / GMT First disclosure of original study: Date not specified in study / Time not specified in study / Time zone not specified in study----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: CAPGEMINI :  Oddo raises its 2023 growth forecasts
full_text: Oddo reports that Capgemini yesterday morning published Q4 sales of 5754 ME, 2% ahead of expectations. Organic growth came in at +12.8% y/y, ahead of expectations (Consensus: +10.8%; Oddo BHF: +12.8%e). The analyst points out that only North America performed below expectations (12.3% y/y vs. 14.0% y/y for Oddo), due to the Tech sector.For the full year 2022, non-IFRS operating income stands at 2867 ME, in line with expectations, implying a margin of 13.0%, up 10 bp (Oddo BHF and Consensus: 13.0%e). Oddo raises its guidance for 2023 organic growth to 5.6% (vs. 4.4%) and Op Margin to 13.2% (vs. 13.1%), towards the upper end of the Group's guidance range. The short target has been raised to 226 E (vs. 218 E). Oddo reiterates its outperform rating on the stock, motivated by its low valuation.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: UBS lowers target for K+S to 21 euros - 'Neutral
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX Broker) - Swiss major bank UBS cut its price target for K+S to 21 euros from 22 euros in the wake of an analyst change and left its rating at "neutral". The fertilizer group's balance sheet should be strongly supported in the short term, as K+S is generating above-cycle earnings and potash prices are likely to remain high for now, new analyst Priyanka Patel wrote in a research note issued Wednesday. In the longer term, however, profitability in Europe could be threatened by structurally higher energy costs and downside risks to potash prices, as Belarus, an important producer country affected by Western sanctions, could open up other export routes over time./edh/mis  Publication of the original study: 22.02.2023 / 00:57 / GMT First disclosure of the original study: 22.02.2023 / 00:57 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: BNP PARIBAS  :  Berenberg raises its price target
full_text: On Wednesday, Berenberg raised its price target for BNP Paribas from €55 to €70, while renewing its 'hold' recommendation on the stock.In a research note, the analyst points out that the French banking group has slightly outperformed its French peers on the stock market over the past 12 months.Although he points out that the company's development prospects are not as promising as those of the rest of the sector, the intermediary believes that its "diversified" business model limits the share's downward potential.As for its capital level, it is currently far from excessive from Berenberg's point of view, which in his view limits the scenario of major redistributions to shareholders.While BNP remains his preferred banking stock, the professional believes that its current valuation level - which he judges to be in line with its historical discount of 10% to the rest of the sector - adequately reflects its prospects in terms of earnings growth.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: CAPGEMINI :  Invest Securities raises price target
full_text: Invest Securities has reiterated its 'buy' rating on Capgemini, with the price target raised from €200 to €220, offering potential upside of +21%, after the IT services group's 2022 financial year was judged to be 'very high-flying'.'Capgemini is in a very comfortable position to enter the 2023 financial year, which will not be as exciting, but which could hold some pleasant surprises, especially in view of the cautious guidance provided by management', the analyst believes. title: ENGIE  :  Oddo slightly raises its target
full_text: Oddo maintains its Outperform rating on Engie shares, with a price target raised from 17 to 18 euros. The research firm reports that Engie's results published yesterday for fiscal year 2022 were in line with guidance but slightly ahead of expectations. EBITDA rose 27% organically to €13,665m (vs. guidance of €13.2-14.2 bn), while Oddo and the consensus were expecting €13,349m and €13,320m respectively.The Group has revised upwards its forecasts for 2023-24, with EBIT expected at 6.6-7.6 BnE in 2023 and 7.2-8.2 BnE in 2024, and recurring net income expected at 3.4-4.0 BnE in 2023 and 3.8-4.4 BnE in 2024. In this context, 'we have raised our earnings estimate partly on the basis of the acceleration of the Capex plan from E22-24bn over the period 2021-23 to E29-33bn over the period 2023-25', says Oddo. title: Barclays raises target for Covestro to 60 euros - 'Overweight
full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX Broker) - British investment bank Barclays raised its price target for Covestro from 56 to 60 euros and left its rating at "Overweight". title: AIR FRANCE-KLM :  UBS raises its price target
full_text: On Tuesday, UBS renewed its buy recommendation on Air France-KLM, with a new target price of 2.2 euros, up from two euros previously, representing a potential upside of 29%."Despite an almost 40% gain in the share price since the start of the year, we continue to recommend buying the stock", explains the broker in a research note.We believe that the continued improvement in earnings, driven by a recovery in passenger traffic (driven by the upturn in business travel, the reopening of Asia and continuing strong demand in leisure) and solid pricing (underpinned by capacity discipline), should support the share price", continues UBS.In addition, the company expects its unit costs excluding fuel to remain stable, whereas we see them declining, suggesting that the risk of positive surprises is on the upside', he concludes.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: VINCI :  RBC raises its target price
full_text: On Tuesday, RBC reiterated its 'overweight' recommendation on Vinci shares, with a new target price of 125 euros, up from 110 euros previously, showing a potential upside of 14%.In a research note, the Canadian broker justifies the target upgrade by the better-than-expected 2022 full-year results published by the French construction and concessions giant, as well as the stake taken in Mexican airport group OMA.RBC notes that investors are generally positive about Vinci, but that some are dubious about the potential for value creation in the renewable energies sector.While praising the French group's 'resilient' and 'diversified' status, the broker points out that investors are concerned about the impact of inflationary pressures on its construction business, despite the optimistic forecasts for 2023 provided by the management team.In terms of valuation, the professional underlines that the stock is trading on the basis of 8x its Enterprise Value/Ebitda ratio to 2024, a discount to its historical average of 9x.The stock remains its top pick within the transportation infrastructure sector.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: AIR FRANCE-KLM :  Barclays initiates 'overweight' rating
full_text: Barclays initiated coverage of Air France-KLM shares on Monday evening with an 'overweight' recommendation and a target price of 2.3 euros, highlighting the airline's improving balance sheet.In a study of the sector, Barclays believes that Air France-KLM should be able to take advantage of the strength of demand, but also of its internal restructuring.From a sector point of view, the analyst considers that the catching-up of demand - combined with the reopening of Asian economies and corporate travel - should more than outweigh the economic slowdown.The intermediary points out that he will be closely monitoring activity indicators to determine when the sector will be able to return to its pre-pandemic levels, given that it is currently very close to them.For the time being, what really matters, in our view, is the level of profitability that European airlines can post", he adds.As part of its rating, Barclays has also begun monitoring Lufthansa and Ryanair, with a favorable recommendation.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: Oddo maintains its 'neutral' rating on Air France-KLM shares, with its price target raised from 1.65 to 2.1 euros.'Following the publication of Q4 and 2023 targets, we have revised upwards our EBIT estimates of 26%/20%/16% respectively for 2023/24/25', says the broker. The load factor stands at 80% for Q1 2023 bookings and 39% for Q2 bookings, versus 82% and 42% for the same period in 2019."We have raised our yield estimates to +3% vs. 2022", adds Oddo, which believes that the very gradual reopening of routes to China should also help overall yield in the short term. title: HERMÈS :  Oddo raises its price target
full_text: Hermès has reported sales for fiscal year 2022 of 11,602 ME, up +23% cc, and EBIT of 4,697 ME, representing a margin of 40.5%.Oddo's forecasts were 11,406 ME and 4,464 ME respectively (margin 39.1%), while the Visible Alpha consensus was 11,427 ME and 4,555 ME (margin just under 40%).  Full-year sales exceeded consensus expectations by 2%, and the EBIT margin was 3%, highlighting an excellent performance at the end of the year", said the analyst.  In the Asia-Pacific region, Hermès continued to enjoy double-digit growth in China, with the Group feeling the effects of the COVID disruption much less than its competitors. The group reported net income, group share of €3,367m (Oddo was expecting €3,143m), and its net cash position passed the €9bn mark at the end of 2022 (it stood at c. €6.7bn at the end of 2021).' No break in the trend entering 2023, but a still cautious message on margins, we are nevertheless raising our EBIT forecasts by +2%' adds Oddo.Oddo confirms its Outperform recommendation on the stock and raises its target price from E1,794 to E1,854.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: HERMÈS :  Invest Securities raises its target
full_text: Invest Securities maintains its 'sell' recommendation on Hermès shares, with a price target raised from 1030 to 1385 euros. According to the analyst, "Hermès has achieved a 2022 financial year that reinforces its uniqueness through the quality of the results obtained, and above all their regularity, which contrasts with a certain volatility of performance within the sector". The consensus forecast was for operating income of E4.55 billion and net income of E3.2 billion, whereas Hermès posted EBIT of E4.7 billion (+33%) and net income of E3.4 billion (+38%). Nevertheless, "whether or not we are behind the consensus, we still come up against the same problem of a valuation that we are unable to justify", says Invest.  The constrained management of scarcity in leather goods is a limiting factor for production and therefore demand, but above all it doesn't really seem to us to be in tune with the times", he concludes. title: AIRBUS :  BofA raises its price target
full_text: Bank of America announced on Friday that it had raised its price target for Airbus from 185 to 200 euros, while maintaining its buy recommendation on the stock.In a research note, the financial intermediary acknowledges that the European aircraft manufacturer's supply chain remains tense, but stresses that it is tending to improve.Above all, the acceleration in production rates for the A350 and A330 is a particularly encouraging factor, writes the analyst in his study.While BofA has reduced its earnings forecasts for 2023, the professional has revised upwards its estimates for 2025 based on the new delivery targets communicated by the Group.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Airbus: in the green with broker's comments
full_text: Airbus is in the green, gaining less than 1% and outperforming the trend in Paris, helped by favorable comments from Stifel, which reiterates its 'buy' recommendation with a price target raised from 14% to 160 euros on the aircraft manufacturer's stock.According to the broker, 'Airbus offers strong EPS growth at reasonable multiples, good cash flow beyond 2023, with a leading position in a duopolistic market and low reinvestment requirements'.Bank of America also confirms its 'buy' recommendation, with its target price raised from 185 to 200 euros, while Oddo BHF maintains its 'outperform' rating, with its target price raised from 139 to 145 euros.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: ACCOR :  Oddo raises its target price
full_text: On Friday, Oddo maintained its 'outperform' rating on Accor shares, while raising its target price from €33 to €36."Accor should be reassuring on the operating front in upcoming publications, thanks to the continuing hotel rebound and its RESET cost-savings plan", notes the analyst in a research note.And even if visibility is still limited for 2023, 'the recovery in the hotel business, strong domestic exposure, the acceleration of independent hoteliers' conversions to chain hotels and Accor's solid financial stance', reassures Oddo.The intermediary says it particularly appreciates 'Accor's significant exposure to management contracts (56% of the portfolio vs. 41% in franchises), which offer additional operating leverage'.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: AIRBUS :  Oddo raises its price target
full_text: Oddo confirms its 'outperform' rating on Airbus shares, with its price target raised from 139 to 145 euros. The analyst cites relief regarding the 2023 fiscal year, with "2023 targets that are admittedly below consensus expectations, but which we believe exceed the fears of most investors". In addition, 'relief is also visible with regard to the ultimately relatively limited consequences of inflation, with an impact of a few hundred ME according to management', continues Oddo. For 2023, the broker is targeting adjusted EBIT of 6,310 ME and adjusted FCF of 3,485 ME for 735 deliveries. We believe that the possibility of launching a share buyback program will come to the fore at the end of the year, once the Reload plan has been finalized and the CFO's transition phase has ended", it adds. Against this backdrop, Oddo is revising its short-term EPS guidance downwards (-1.9% and -2.9% in 2023 and 2024 respectively), but is raising it beyond that, to take account of a slight increase in long-haul production rates, notably for the A350.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: SCHNEIDER ELECTRIC :  Oddo raises its target price
full_text: Oddo maintains its Outperform rating on Schneider Electric shares, with its price target raised from 169 to 179 euros. Yesterday, the company published 2022 results slightly ahead of expectations, with organic growth of 12.2% for 2022 (vs. 10.2% expected by consensus and 10.1% by ODDO BHF) and 16% for Q4 alone, including 5% volume growth.  The 2023 guidance was well above expectations on organic growth (9-11% target vs. 2.8% expected by consensus). However, we consider the EBITA margin guidance to be disappointing, with a target change of -20/+10 bp, i.e. 17.4%/17.7% (consensus 17.8%)', notes the analyst. Against this backdrop, Oddo is raising its EPS guidance by 2% on average over 2023 and 2024, and anticipates organic sales growth of 9.1% in 2023 (vs. 3.5% previously).  The Group should continue to benefit from its excellent positioning in electrification and energy efficiency, which will support volumes in 2023 and over the medium term", the broker believes. title: DZ Bank raises fair value for Südzucker to 17.60 euros - 'Buy
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - DZ Bank raised the fair value for Südzucker from 17.10 to 17.60 euros and left its rating at "buy". The sugar producer has raised its earnings forecast for the fourth time in the past ten months, analyst Axel Herlinghaus wrote in a research note presented on Thursday. The latest higher assumption for operating profit (Ebit) is likely to come from energy costs. However, these remained a relevant component of uncertainty against the backdrop of the ongoing war in Ukraine. Nevertheless, in purely quantitative terms, gas supplies had eased considerably in view of the adequate German storage levels. In his view, the "sugar lights" for the coming twelve months are "clearly green". Operationally, the recent rise in ethanol prices to more than 800 euros per cubic meter has also improved the business prospects for the CropEnergies and Agrana starch holdings. However, it is important to keep an eye on further developments in the political environment, especially the Mercosur agreement./bek/la  Publication of the original study: 16.02.2023 / 13:12 / CET First disclosure of the original study: 16.02.2023 / 13:27 / CET----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: FDJ :  Oddo slightly raises its target
full_text: Oddo maintains its 'neutral' rating on Française des Jeux (FDJ), with a target price raised from €37.5 to €38.5. FDJ published good results for 2022, broadly in line with expectations. Nevertheless, the share price has been hit quite hard on the stock market (-5.4% at close), probably due to the disappointment over the dividend (1.37 E per share, 4% below expectations)', estimates Oddo. This stock market reaction is judged 'severe' by the analyst, particularly in view of the Group's results and its outlook for 2023. Oddo also points out that the European Commission's investigation into the amount of the balancing payment made by FDJ to the French state at the time of privatization should continue to weigh on the equity story. Management hopes for a decision in 2023, but the procedure could be lengthy, especially with possible appeals.  For 2023, FDJ expects sales growth of 4/5%, based on a pro forma landing in 2022 at 2,514 ME, which includes the acquisitions of Aleda and Addition, implying a sales range of 2,615 / 2,640 ME for 2023 according to our estimates', reports the analyst firm. title: BIC :  Oddo confirms its recommendation on the share
full_text: Oddo maintains its 'neutral' rating on Bic with an unchanged target price of 73 euros, judging that the group published 'contrasting' results for the 4th quarter. In the last three months of the year, Bic reported sustained sales growth, to 526.7 ME, or +9.1% on a comparable basis, but also a more disappointing adjusted operating income of 43.2 ME, or 15.8% below Oddo's estimate.  We note that most of the difference with our Q4 ROC estimates is due to the Paper Division, which posted ROC of -8.9 ME, compared with 2 ME," stresses the analyst. At the same time, the lighters business grew by +10.9% on a comparable basis, while shavers were up +16.4%...'For 2023, management has indicated that it expects sales growth at constant exchange rates of between 5% and 7%, which is slightly higher than our expectations (+4.9%) and those of the consensus (4.6%)', reports the broker.  All in all, this publication does not change our perception", he concludes. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Barclays raises target for Siemens to 126 euros - 'Underweight
full_text: LONDON (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.K.-based investment bank Barclays raised its price target for Siemens to 126 euros from 120 euros, but left its rating at "underweight." The ending quarterly reporting season for Europe's capital goods maker showed continued demand and a surprisingly strong outlook for 2023, analyst Lars Brorson wrote in an industry report Wednesday. But the cyclical upside potential already appears fully priced in, he added. For Siemens, Brorson raised adjusted earnings estimates (Ebita) after the first-quarter figures./gl/edh      Publication of the original study: 14.02.2023 / 19:19 / GMT First circulation of the original study: 15.02.2023 / 05:00 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: UBS downgrades Software AG to 'Neutral' and targets 22.20 euros
full_text: ZURICH (dpa-AFX Broker) - Major Swiss bank UBS downgraded Software AG to "neutral" from "buy" and cut its price target to 22.20 euros from 37.00 euros. Capital expenditures are likely to weigh on the software maker in 2023, analyst Michael Briest wrote in a research note issued Wednesday. Another year of marginal cash flow is looming, so even at Software AG, dividends cannot be taken for granted, he added. The transformation toward the cloud has just begun, he said, and headwinds to growth and margins could persist beyond 2023. Briest therefore misses share price drivers, notwithstanding a low valuation, and lowered his earnings estimates (EPS)./gl/edh      Publication of the original study: 14.02.2023 / 18:28 / GMT First disclosure of the original study: 14.02.2023 / 18:28 / GMT----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

full_text: Invest Securities maintains its 'neutral' rating on Carrefour shares, with a slightly reduced target price of 17.7 euros, compared with 18 euros previously. full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. bank JPMorgan has upgraded Thyssenkrupp from "Underweight" to "Neutral" after quarterly figures and raised the price target from 5.70 to 5.90 euros. title: MTU weak after figures and outlook - Dax end
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - MTU shares, which have performed strongly in recent months, fell sharply on Tuesday following figures and an outlook. Down 2.1 percent to 222.50 euros in the early afternoon, they were far and away at the bottom of the Dax.      By the beginning of February, the engine manufacturer's shares had more than halved in price in the space of three months, boosted by an optimistic forecast in the fall. Profit-taking then caused the share price to crumble somewhat in February. On Tuesday, the shares fell back to their lowest price in a good month. Even the highest dividend in the group's history, which beckons to shareholders for 2022, could not change that.      MTU's key figures for the fourth quarter and the full year 2022 presented a mixed picture, wrote analyst Holger Schmidt of DZ Bank in a study. For the expert, however, the better-than-expected profit and free cash flow development is more important than the revenue momentum, which, although strong, was nevertheless somewhat lower than expected. The lowering of the sales outlook is probably mainly due to the adjustment of the euro/dollar exchange rate./ajx/stk----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: DZ Bank lowers Adidas to 'Hold' and fair value to 138 euros
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - DZ Bank downgraded Adidas from "buy" to "hold" and lowered the fair value from 155 to 138 euros. In addition, the financial institution removed the securities of the sporting goods manufacturer from the "DZ Bank Equity Ideas" recommendation list. "The fact that a new CEO clears the air and starts in office with conservative targets is basically no surprise," analyst Thomas Maul wrote in a study available on Monday. However, he said the market was negatively surprised by the announced operating loss (Ebit) of up to 700 million euros. The disappointing forecast is explained on the one hand by the very likely scenario in which Adidas no longer sells any products by the rapper Kanye West (Yeezy brand), who is controversial because of anti-Semitic statements, and on the other hand by the fact that the consensus estimates have so far probably not taken sufficient account of the fact that Adidas has not been able to sell any products at all.The second reason is the one-off restructuring expenses, which have probably not been sufficiently taken into account in the consensus estimates to date, as well as burdens from the reduction of excess inventories and challenging market conditions in China. The chances are good that Adidas will return to the path of success with Björn Gulden. However, this is likely to take somewhat longer than previously assumed./gl/la      Publication of the original study: 13.02.2023 / 07:49 / CET First disclosure of the original study: 13.02.2023 / 07:58 / CET----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: CEMENTIR HOLDING  :  FY 22: Price hikes to manage inflation.
full_text:
FY 22: Price hikes to manage inflation.EARNINGS/SALES RELEASESCementir has published better than expected preliminary FY22 results with revenue 13% and EBITDA 6% above our expectations. However, for FY23, the group has guided for a conservative outlook due to an uncertain macroeconomic scenario and announced a new industrial Plan to highlight its commitment to decarbonization.FACT
Revenue: €1,723.1m, up 27%
EBITDA: €335.2m, up 7.8% (€337.2m excluding one-offs)
EBIT: €206.3m, up 4.3%
Guidance for 2023: Revenue of more than €1.8bn, EBITDA at €335-345m, net cash position above €200m, capex ~€113m.
Industrial Plan 2023-2025 announced.ANALYSISCementir Holding has published better than expected FY22 results with revenues up by 27% to €1,723m, driven by price increases across all geographies despite a decrease in volumes sales in all segments. Cement sales decreased by 2.7%, RMC by 5.8% and Aggregates by 5.3%. The general slowdown in the market did not prevent the company from achieving a record EBITDA of €335m (+14.2%), including a one-off positive impact of €17.8m related to real estate. Even after excluding this one-off event, the actual EBITDA is slightly above our expectations. However, the EBITDA margin decreased by 200bp to reach 20.6%. 
Conservative forecast in 2023
The uncertainty of the macroeconomic scenario is forcing the company to be prudent on their outlook for the year 2023. Cementir Holding expects to achieve consolidated revenues of roughly €1.8bn (+4%) with flat growth in EBITDA. Indeed, the company expects a decline in demand resulting in a drop in volume sales, and Cementir would not be able to hike its prices as it did in 2022 unless there is a skyrocketing increase in the carbon price and electricity as the price mechanism of the company is correlated to these costs. However, the company has succeeded in managing its costs and maintaining its margins in 2022 thanks to its strong cost management. We expect Cementir will maintain this efficient cost management in 2023. 
Industrial Plan 2023-2025
The group has updated its Industrial Plan, which revolves around the same pillars as before, but with a further commitment to the decarbonization, less aggressive financial targets for the revenue (CAGR of 5.1% vs 6.7% previously) and a better outlook for EBITDA (CAGR of 5.9% vs 5.3% previously). With additional cumulative green capex of €86m, the company is focusing on projects enabling a reduction in carbon emissions. In our sense, the two key levers to achieve the fit to 55 targets set by EU are (i) clinker content reduction and (ii) Carbon capture and storage (CCS) technologies. Cementir has started a pilot project for CCS partly financed by the Danish Innovation Fund and plans to have a clinker ratio of 64% for the grey cement as well as 78% for the white cement by 2030. This puts the company in an advantageous position to address carbon emissions issues.IMPACTFollowing these results, we have updated upwards our model and maintain our positive recommendation. Our target price has been increased by 5% supported by an increase in 2022 EPS (+0.09€), 2023 EPS (+0.08€) and a higher DCF valuation (+0.93€).

title: CEMENTIR HOLDING  :  EPS upgrade (2022: +10.6%, 2023: +9.3%)
full_text: EPS CHANGECHANGE IN EPS2022 : € 0.90 vs 0.81 +10.6%2023 : € 0.95 vs 0.87 +9.30%We have updated our model following the better than expected preliminary FY22 results. The EPS 2022 is up by €0.09 and the EPS 2023 forecast is increased by €0.08, driven by high price increases leading to 13% higher revenue and 6% higher EBITDA than in our previous estimates. CHANGE IN DCF€ 13.7 vs 12.8 +7.29%The strong growth reported this year has enabled an upwards revision to our sales estimates even in a conservative scenario due to the uncertain macroeconomic situation. Since we have increased our 2024 EBITDA forecast, which is the base value for the DCF, the overall valuation has risen, leading to a 5% increase in our Target Price to €11.25.

title: Berenberg lowers Siltronic to 'Hold' and target to 91 euros
full_text: HAMBURG (dpa-AFX Broker) - Private bank Berenberg downgraded Siltronic from "buy" to "hold" and lowered its price target from 95 to 91 euros. After double-digit percentage increases in wafer prices last year, which could have offset high energy costs and inflation at Siltronic, the situation has now changed, analyst Gustav Froberg wrote in a research note presented on Monday. Customer inventories appeared to be growing amid weaker demand for consumer electronics, posing risks to the wafer maker's near-term results, he said. title: EURONEXT :  BofA remains Buy, target 118 euros
full_text: On Friday, Bank of America maintained its Buy recommendation on Euronext, with a price target of 118 euros, after the company's annual results were described as "decent".In a reaction note, the broker emphasizes that the stock market operator's performance last year was modestly above consensus, while noting that its synergy target for 2024 has been revised upwards from 100 to 115 million euros.According to the broker, most of the good news stems from the integration of Borsa Italiana, which it considers to be the key element of the deal."The acquisition of Borsa Italiana, when completed, will make Euronext a better company from our point of view", writes BofA in the note.The professional considers that Euronext is already the undisputed leader in IPOs and cash transactions in Europe, but points out that from the end of 2024 it will benefit from an integrated derivatives platform that it can in turn grow."We continue to believe that Euronext is undervalued, with market sentiment ignoring the positive effects of integration", he continues."With a share price trading at 12.5 times expected earnings next year, a significant discount to peers, we believe the stock offers clear potential for value creation", concludes BofA.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. full_text: On Friday, Jefferies initiated coverage of Soitec's shares with a "hold" recommendation and a price target of 145 euros, explaining that it sees a number of short-term difficulties for the semiconductor materials manufacturer.While it sees several catalysts in the medium term that could help the group to do better than expected by 2026, the broker expects lacklustre growth in the shorter term, against a backdrop of deteriorating demand.According to Jefferies, the mobile business in particular is the most vulnerable for the 2023/2024 financial year, due to the current weakness in smartphone volumes and inventory adjustments by customers.With an EPS forecast for 2023/2024 2% below consensus and a PER of 14x, the broker indicates that, at best, there is limited upside potential in the short term.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Carl Zeiss Meditec turns positive - UBS praises sales growth
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - The medical technology group Carl Zeiss Meditec defied the rather moderate start to the new fiscal year on Friday: The shares quickly shook off their pre-market weakness with the start of trading and most recently gained around half a percent to 131.20 euros.      This also marked the end of a four-day losing streak - at the low for the day right at the start of trading, the loss had totaled ten percent. The current annual gain of the share amounts to around 11 percent, which means that Carl Zeiss lags a little behind the MDax of medium-sized companies.      Due to increased costs and problems in China, the company reported a significant drop in earnings before interest and taxes (Ebit) in the first fiscal quarter. In addition to higher expenses for sales and marketing, for example, as well as for research and development, the decline in eye surgeries in China put pressure on the margin, which was even weaker than feared, according to a stock exchange expert. Life came to a standstill in many places in the country due to the Covid outbreak towards the end of 2022.      On the other hand, very strong sales were above the consensus estimate, commented analyst Graham Doyle of Swiss bank UBS. The first quarter is also likely to prove the weakest of the fiscal year. Doyle is betting on a recovery in China and further easing in supply chains, and sees upside potential in the mid-single-digit percentage range for market earnings estimates. He also said there was room for upside in organic sales growth forecasts. The expert maintained his "buy" rating with a target price of 156 euros, to which the share has a margin of just under 19 percent./gl/ag/stk

title: CARMAT :  Degroof Petercam adjusts its price target
full_text: On Friday, Degroof Petercam maintained its buy recommendation on Carmat, while slightly adjusting its price target from €20.5 to €20.2.In a note published in the morning, the Belgian investment house considers that the artificial heart manufacturer has "only a few more steps to go before a beautiful landscape emerges".Degroof, which recently organized a conference dedicated to the healthcare sector, points out that the French company took the opportunity to confirm its forecasts, i.e. sales of between 10 and 13 million euros this year, a commercial launch in the USA scheduled for 2026, and breakeven financial results in 2027.In terms of operational targets, Carmat says it is aiming to produce 100 Aeson systems in 2023, 500 in 2024 and 1,000 by 2027."Market demand does not seem to be a problem, but ramping up production to meet demand and targets could be a real challenge", says Degroof Petercam.The Brussels-based firm explains that it has modified some of its forecasts to take into account the sales breakdown indications communicated by the company, as well as the expected evolution of its investments and operating expenses.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: LEGRAND :  Oddo raises its target price
full_text: Oddo maintains its 'neutral' rating on Legrand shares, with a price target raised from 84 to 86 euros, after Legrand yesterday morning published Q4 2022 results 'quite significantly above expectations'.The research firm reports that the CEO did not wish to comment on market prospects, but believes that datacenters (which were very dynamic in 2022) and green products will continue to grow.   We now forecast organic sales growth of 0.6% (including -1.3% in volumes) and an adjusted EBIT margin of 19.7% for 2023. This compares with organic growth targets of -1/+3% and a margin of around 20% before the impact of acquisitions and Russia", says Oddo.Finally, the analyst reports that most groups in the sector (Assa Abloy, Rexel, Schneider Electric, etc.) should be able to generate much more sustained growth, thanks to their positioning in more buoyant segments (electrification, automation, etc.). title: Deutsche Bank Research rates Adidas 'Buy' - Target 170 euros
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Deutsche Bank Research left its rating on Adidas at "buy" with a price target of 170 euros. The sporting goods maker dropped the hammer on its 2023 forecast far more than investors expected, analyst Adam Cochrane wrote in a research note issued Friday. While there had been a risk that a new CEO would take a more conservative approach, he said expectations had now been revised down more significantly compared to the range that had been set out in the outlook. If you want to look on the bright side, you could say that everything negative is now on the table and that expectations could therefore be exceeded again in the future. Nevertheless, more clarity is needed first with regard to earnings power and how the lower base for 2023 will impact 2024 and the longer-term forecasts. Consensus estimates for operating profit (Ebit) in 2024 and 2025 are expected to fall by 20 percent. Similar declines are expected for the share price, he added./ajx/edh      Publication of original study: 10.02.2023 / Time not specified in study / CET First disclosure of original study: 10.02.2023 / 07:02 / CET----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: LEGRAND :  Oddo confirms its recommendation on the stock
full_text: Oddo maintains its 'neutral' rating on Legrand shares, with an unchanged target price of 84 euros. This morning, Legrand published better-than-expected results for 2022 in terms of organic growth, with an increase of 9.7%, including 8.5% for Q4 alone (the consensus was 5.0%). Net income for 2022 rose by 10.5% to ME1,000, and the Group intends to propose a dividend of E1.9 (+15%). It also announces a share buyback program of up to 500 ME over 18 months, reports Oddo. For 2023, Legrand forecasts organic growth of between -1% and +3% (2-6% including 3% impact of acquisitions) and an adjusted EBIT margin of around 20%. While a conference call with management is scheduled for today, Oddo indicates that it will be attentive to comments on current or future inflexions in demand, particularly in the residential sector, as well as on distributor inventory levels. title: UBS downgrades Scout24 after share price increase due to real estate market weakness
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX) - Growing concerns about the German real estate market make Scout24  shares less attractive in the view of major Swiss bank UBS. UBS analyst Adam Berlin, referring to the latest data on the German housing market, expects demand for real estate to be historically weak this year, according to a study published Wednesday. This is also likely to lead to a decline in transactions in the core areas of the operator of Internet portals, he said.      Prices for houses and apartments are already falling, while at the same time there are more and more properties for sale, it said. Average analyst estimates (consensus) for Scout24 in 2023 are therefore likely to fall, Berlin wrote. However, he has not changed his own estimates, the expert stressed. Therefore, he also left his price target for the share of the MDax-listed company unchanged at 57.30 euros. However, following the 15 percent rise in the share price since the beginning of the year, he now downgraded it from "buy" to "neutral". From Berlin's point of view, it is thus valued in line with the industry.      Scout24 shares then fell by around 2.8 percent to 52.98 euros and also fell below the 200-day average line as a measure of the longer-term trend.       According to the analyst, however, the growing dependence of brokers on the Immoscout24 online platform, which would have to continue to find buyers in a difficult market environment, speaks in favor of the company. Scout24 would also benefit from advertisements for properties being online on the marketplace for a longer period of time. On top of that, the analyst expects continued strong growth in subscriptions from private individuals. With a so-called Plus membership, users are granted privileges in the search, so that they can, for example, contact the seller or landlord with priority.      Scout24's core business, however, is brokerage memberships, which accounted for nearly half of the group's revenue in the third quarter. In 2023, however, Berlin expects a higher churn of brokers than customers and, as a result, its revenue estimate for this year and next is below consensus. Scout24 plans to present preliminary figures for the final quarter on Feb. 28 and most recently targeted the upper end of its revenue and earnings forecast for 2022 as a whole.      With a rating of "Neutral", UBS assumes that the total return of the share (price gain plus dividend) on a twelve-month horizon will be up to six percent above or below the market return expected by UBS./niw/ck/tih  Analyzing institute UBS.      Publication of the original study: 08.02.2023 / 01:10 / GMT     First disclosure of the original study: 08.02.2023 / 01:10 / GMT

title: CARREFOUR :  Oddo confirms its price target
full_text: Oddo reports that the PGC FLS market share data for P1 (December 25, 2022 to January 22, 2023) are available (Kantar), and show a slight increase for Carrefour.  The Group gained +0.1% in supermarket format and +0.1% in convenience, while hypermarkets remained stable, for a total of +0.2%. This level matches that of Leclerc, Aldi and Lidl (+0.2% each). The Group also gained customers over the period (+320k) and recorded strong traffic levels', says the analyst. Oddo also points out that the situation is as bad as ever for Casino, which is losing 0.5% market share. This is broken down into -0.1% from Monoprix and -0.4% from hypermarkets.  We think that management will insist on a rather difficult H1, and a H2 with a priori less inflation and a more favorable basis of comparison, whereas the seasonality of H2 historically accounts for almost two-thirds of ROI," adds the research firm. Oddo confirms its Outperform recommendation and its target price of E19, and believes that market share momentum is encouraging. Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: SANOFI :  Oddo slightly reduces its target
full_text: Oddo maintains its 'outperform' rating on Sanofi shares, with a price target reduced from 107 to 105 euros. The research firm reports that Q4 results have put the stock under pressure. Oddo highlights two points: i/ an overall cautious guidance for 2023 (although in line with tcc, in our opinion) and ii/ questions about Tolebrutinib. According to Oddo, this year will be the most "challenging" for Sanofi, with the loss of the Aubagio patent on the one hand, and the launch of Altuviiio and Beyfortus on the other."We remain convinced by Sanofi's story, and the recent pressure on the share price accentuates the investment opportunity", says the broker.  With a PE at a 25% discount to the sector average, the PEG is very attractive. A short-term success for Dupixent in COPD would be the catalyst for the start of a rerating', concludes the analyst. title: Legrand: share price down, broker adjusts his recommendation
full_text: Legrand is down nearly 1% in Paris, as Deutsche Bank on Tuesday downgraded its recommendation on the stock from 'buy' to 'hold', with an unchanged target price of 86 euros.In a research note, the financial intermediary explains that the electrical equipment manufacturer is currently trading on the basis of an Enterprise Value/Ebita ratio of 14.5x and a PER of 20x, figures in line with its historical multiples.Under these conditions, the analyst says he sees only limited upside potential for the share at current levels.From an operational point of view, Deutsche Bank says it fears that demand will be affected by a sharper-than-expected correction in the residential construction sector.The professional also fears that the Group's management will communicate cautious forecasts for the 2023 financial year, particularly in view of the recent decision to leave the Russian market, which still accounted for 1.5% of sales last year. title: VETOQUINOL :  Stifel lowers its target price
full_text: On Tuesday, Stifel reiterated its Buy recommendation on Vetoquinol, while lowering its target price for the stock from 145 to 112 euros, which still represents a potential upside of around 30%.Despite the somewhat disappointing performance recently posted by the veterinary pharmaceutical laboratory, the intermediary believes that the company's strategy of tightening its business portfolio should eventually bear fruit.According to him, the focus on the 'Essential' product range - which already accounts for 56% of sales - should lead to an improvement in gross margin.Stifel thus expects the animal health specialist's results to recover, anticipating average annual sales growth of 10% over the 2022-2026 period.The stock also remains his preferred stock within the sector.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: VIRBAC :  Stifel raises its recommendation to 'buy
full_text: Stifel announced on Tuesday that it had raised its recommendation on Virbac shares from 'hold' to 'buy', with a price target reduced from 402 to 342 euros.In a note dedicated to the animal health sector, the analyst considers that the current share price of the French pharmaceutical laboratory does not reflect the turnaround it has managed to achieve over the last five years.Nor, in his opinion, does its stock market valuation take into account the improvement in business linked to the Covid-19 crisis, or the effect of the sale of the Sentinel brand, which has enabled the company to reduce its debt and invest in its capacities in order to relaunch its growth.According to Stifel, the Group is in a position to aim for average annual sales growth of around 8.1% over the period 2021-2026, accompanied by a stabilization of its operating margin above 19% by 2030.With the strategic reorientation of its product portfolio towards blockbusters, the development of its animal feed range and the acceleration of its vaccine activities, Stifel expects Virbac to generate average annual EPS growth of 9% by 2026.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Oddo BHF downgrades Synlab to 'Underperform' - Target down to 9.50
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - Investment bank Oddo BHF downgraded Synlab by two notches from "outperform" to "underperform" and lowered its price target from 13.50 euros to 9.50 euros after a profit warning. Covid testing revenue should decline more significantly in 2023 than he thought, analyst Christophe-Raphael Ganet wrote in a research note issued Tuesday. He cut his own assumption for the lab services provider and expects market expectations to fall as well. He also called the expected decline in contribution from acquisitions a disappointment. In addition, production gains would probably be wiped out by inflation. On the negative side, there would also be dilutive effects from direct business with end consumers and a service provider contract in the UK./tav/tih  Publication of the original study: 07.02.2023 / 08:31 / CET First disclosure of the original study: 07.02.2023 / 08:37 / CET----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: RENAULT :  Invest Securities remains Buy after the agreement
full_text: Invest Securities reaffirms its 'buy' opinion and 54 euro price target on Renault, after the outcome of negotiations with Nissan 'was reached without any major surprises between the CMD 'Revolution' in November 2022 and the 2022 publication on February 16'.In this perspective, our estimates for BNA 2022/23/24 move by +11% /-0%/-1% on a publication expected to be slightly above the 2022 EBITA margin guidance (over 5%) and in anticipation of its stability in 2023", the analyst adds. title: SANOFI :  Credit Suisse forecasts for 2023
full_text: Sanofi reported business EPS of 8.26 euros for full-year 2022, up 25.9% (+17.1% at constant exchange rates), and said it had achieved its medium-term targets of operating margin at 30% and cost savings of 2.5 billion euros.' Unfavorable factors are stronger, and forecasts for fiscal 2023 call for only single-digit EPS growth' says the analyst. ' We are cutting EPS for the 2023 business by 6.5%. We forecast EPS growth of 3% for fiscal 2023. We are targeting margins of 32.5% for fiscal 2025, versus forecasts of >32%' adds Credit Suisse.The analyst indicates that Sanofi trades on a 2023 PER of 10.9x, a 31% discount to its European peers. Crédit suisse maintains its Outperform recommendation and price target of 114 E on Sanofi.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: AIRBUS :  Berenberg upgrades to 'sell
full_text: Berenberg announced on Tuesday that it had downgraded its recommendation on Airbus shares from 'hold' to 'sell', with a price target reduced from 120 to 100 euros.In a research note published this morning, the financial intermediary justifies its decision by the effects of inflation on the aircraft manufacturer's results, which it believes are currently poorly taken into account by the financial community.When an order is signed," he points out, "the price of an aircraft is subject to an indexation clause that allows Airbus to raise its rates in line with rising production and labor costs, but not above a certain level.With inflation galloping well beyond the thresholds agreed two years ago, the pricing conditions for a large proportion of the aircraft to be delivered in 2023 and 2024 mean that these orders will have a negative impact on margins, warns the analyst.In its study, Berenberg says it is "surprised" by the forecasts made by analysts, who are aiming for a margin of over 12% by 2025, whereas the group's average over the last 25 years is below 4%.For its part, Berenberg expects operating profit to be between 9% and 15% below consensus estimates for fiscal years 2023, 2024 and 2025.Berenberg had already downgraded its recommendation on Airbus from "buy" to "hold" on January 13.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: RENAULT :  Oddo confirms its Outperform recommendation
full_text: Renault, Nissan and Mitsubishi Motors (MMC), the three Alliance partners, yesterday presented their new agreement. Following this announcement, Oddo confirms its Outperformance recommendation on the stock, with a target price of E55.' The aim of yesterday's presentation was first and foremost to convince everyone that the governance issues had now been dealt with, that the Alliance was back on a much healthier footing, and that operations could therefore, at last, return to the heart of the discussions after several very difficult years in this respect', says Oddo. The analyst also believes that yesterday's priority was to highlight the Alliance's operational revival through new joint projects.  Above all, we see a desire to take advantage of existing industrial bases (South America, India, Europe) and the strengths of the various partners (product segments, technologies).  It seems likely to us that investors will only be ready to value potential synergies when they materialize, i.e. from 2025 for the most part.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: Goldman raises target for Continental AG to €59 - 'Sell
full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - U.S. investment bank Goldman Sachs raised its price target for Continental from 52 to 59 euros, but left its rating at "sell." Demand for replacement tires weakened again in the final quarter, analyst Philipp Konig wrote in an industry report published Tuesday. However, business momentum should normalize from the second quarter. Looking ahead to 2023, however, Konig believes only Michelin can increase profits - he predicts stagnation for Pirelli and a decline for Continental in the tire business./gl/mis      Publication of the original study: 06.02.2023 / 20:33 / GMT First transmission of the original study: Date not specified in study / Time not specified in study / Time zone not specified in study----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

title: DZ Bank downgrades Knorr-Bremse to 'Hold' - Fair value EUR 65
full_text: FRANKFURT (dpa-AFX Broker) - DZ Bank downgraded Knorr-Bremse from "buy" to "hold" and lowered its fair value from EUR 69 to EUR 65. The brake manufacturer is likely to have posted a good annual result, wrote analyst Holger Schmidt in a study presented on Tuesday. However, further rising costs and an improvement in the Chinese rail business, which is only arriving with a delay, made him more cautious for 2023. Based on reduced estimates, the share was trading around 18 percent below the average price of the past four years, but this was justified due to the now weaker growth and lower profitability./edh/tih  Publication of the original study: 07.02.2023 / 08:00 / CET  First disclosure of the original study: 07.02.2023 / 08:05 / CET----------------------- dpa-AFX Broker - the Trader News from dpa-AFX-----------------------

full_text: NEW YORK (dpa-AFX Broker) - Analysts Jefferies has given Brenntag a "hold" rating and a price target of 76 euros. title: LVMH :  Royal Bank of Canada raises its target price
full_text: Royal Bank of Canada announced on Monday that it had raised its target price for LVMH shares from 800 to 890 euros in anticipation of an improvement in the group's profit margin this year.The broker explains that it is maintaining a positive view on the stock, on which it still has an 'outperform' opinion, following the French luxury giant's recently published 2022 annual results.According to RBC, its growth trajectory remains one of the most attractive in the sector, as does its profile in terms of margins and return on capital employed (ROIC).For 2023, the Canadian brokerage forecasts organic growth of 10% and an improvement of one percentage point in its operating margin (Ebit), driven by its investment efforts in marketing, the reopening of the Chinese economy and the recovery of specialized retail chains.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: ESSILORLUXOTTICA :  Bank of America upgrades to buy
full_text: Bank of America announced on Friday that it had upgraded its recommendation on EssilorLuxottica to 'buy' from 'neutral', with a price target raised from 175 to 193 euros.In a research note, the US bank's analysts point out that the eyewear and optical lens manufacturer's share price has risen by just 4% over the last three years, while consumer-related stocks have rebounded by 26% over the same period."The stock is now trading at a PER of 24x, which we consider attractive in view of the group's leading position in a structurally growing market", explains BofA.In addition to this 'attractive' entry price, BofA expects additional synergies of around 300 million euros, plus 450 million euros from the integration of GrandVision, for a total of 750 million euros by 2026.Considering that investors are 'myopic' about the synergies generated by the company, the New York-based firm says it expects average annual earnings per share growth of 9% between now and 2025, accompanied by the payment of some 5.7 billion euros in dividends over the period.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: PUBLICIS :  BofA raises target, maintains buy rating
full_text: Bank of America on Friday maintained its buy recommendation on Publicis, with its price target raised from 82 to 87 euros, believing that the French communications group had finally found its 'mojo' again.In a research note, the research firm said it had revised upwards its earnings forecasts for the company for the 2023/2025 period by between 2% and 4% following the publication of its 2022 annual results.The publication has reinforced our view that organic growth is back at Publicis, and even better than the economy as a whole, which justifies a move to a higher valuation," it points out.BofA also welcomes the outlook for fiscal 2023, which it considers likely to justify upward revisions to analysts' forecasts.The professional, who points out that the stock is trading on a PER of only 11x, makes the share his preferred stock ('key pick') within the sector.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: EssilorLuxottica: share price rises, BofA seduced by valuation
full_text: EssilorLuxottica climbs on the stock market this Friday in the wake of a recommendation upgrade by Bank of America, which considers the stock's valuation attractive in view of its recent underperformance.The US bank's analysts point out that the eyewear and optical lens manufacturer's shares have gained just 4% over the last three years, while consumer-related stocks have rebounded by 26% over the same period.The stock is now trading at a PER of 24x, which we consider attractive in view of the group's leading position in a structurally growing market", explains BofA.Believing that investors are 'short-sighted' when it comes to the synergies generated by the company, the New York-based firm says it expects average annual earnings per share growth of 9% between now and 2025, accompanied by the payment of some 5.7 billion euros in dividends over the period.EssilorLuxottica shares are currently up nearly 3%, the second-highest gain on the CAC 40 behind Publicis.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. All rights reserved.

title: PUBLICIS :  UBS raises its price target
full_text: Publicis announced on Friday that it had raised its target price for Publicis from 71 to 82 euros, following yesterday's solid results and optimistic outlook for the French communications group.The broker - which is reiterating its buy recommendation on the stock - points out that the share is currently trading on the basis of a PER 2023 of 10x, i.e. at a discount of 20% to 25% to its American counterparts, despite significantly higher organic growth.The broker also highlights the group's strong exposure to the USA (over 60% of sales), where the market is more dynamic, as well as the diversification of its revenues thanks to the Publicis Sapient technology platform and marketing subsidiary Epsilon.Finally, UBS hails the company's improved balance sheet situation, expecting it to end the 2023 financial year with net cash of around 680 million euros.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com. title: PUBLICIS :  Barclays raises its recommendation to 'Overweight
full_text: On Friday, Barclays raised its recommendation on Publicis from 'weighted in line' to 'overweight', while raising its target price from €68 to €85.In a research note, the financial intermediary stresses that the advertising and communications group's stock has performed well on the stock market recently, but that its valuation still lags behind.While the share should be trading at a PER 2023 of 14x, in line with the rest of the sector, it is currently trading at around 11x earnings, which seems to Barclays "cheap" in view of the growth posted by the company.According to the professional, Publicis is in a position to generate annual organic growth of around 4%, i.e. annual growth in earnings per share (EPS) of 8%, in line with the sector's historical performance.While Barclays says it has a slight preference for WPP as far as agencies are concerned, it is just as fond of Publicis at present.Copyright (c) 2023 CercleFinance.com.
